menu "Air Purifier Application"

    config STANDALONE_MODE
        bool "Standalone mode (WiFi + Web UI, no Matter)"
        default n
        help
            When enabled, the device operates in standalone mode:
              - Connects to a configured WiFi network (credentials stored in NVS)
              - Runs an HTTP web server on port 80 for fan control
              - Falls back to an open WiFi access point (AirPurifier-XXXXXX) when
                no credentials are stored or the connection fails
              - In AP mode, a configuration page allows entering WiFi credentials
              - The Matter/Thread protocol stack is not started

endmenu
